About the job
Join Centorrino Technologies: Innovate, Grow, and Thrive with Us!

At Centorrino Technologies (CT), we're more than just tech—we're a community that goes beyond expectations. We've been recognised as a Great Place to Work in 2024-2025 and one of the Best Places to Work Medium & Large Size in Australia for 2025, with an outstanding eNPS score of 68. And we're not stopping there. We're on a mission to redefine the customer experience, and we need a passionate Business Analyst to join our team in Australia.

The Business Analyst leads and delivers business analysis activities by eliciting, analysing, and translating stakeholder requirements into fit-for-purpose solutions that support portfolio, program, and project management outcomes and align with organisational P3M frameworks and governance models.

Requirements

What you'll do:

Engage with stakeholders across PMOs and business units to gather, validate, and document business and system requirements 
 Analyse current-state processes and identify opportunities for improvement and optimisation 
 Translate business needs into clear functional and technical specifications for delivery teams 
 Support alignment of systems and processes with P3M frameworks, governance structures, and strategic roadmaps 
 Facilitate workshops, stakeholder meetings, and solution demonstrations to drive consensus and clarity 
 Collaborate closely with technical teams to ensure requirements are accurately interpreted and implemented 
 Support testing activities including UAT planning, execution, and validation of delivered solutions 
 Contribute to continuous improvement initiatives across portfolio and project management practices 
 Produce high-quality documentation including business cases, process maps, and requirements artefacts

What you'll bring:

Demonstrated experience as a Business Analyst within project, program, or portfolio management environments 
 Strong capability in requirements elicitation, analysis, and documentation (e.g. user stories, process maps, functional specs) 
 Experience working within P3M frameworks, governance models, and delivery lifecycles 
 Proven stakeholder engagement and workshop facilitation skills across diverse groups 
 Ability to bridge business and technical teams effectively 
 Experience supporting system implementations or enhancements 
 Experience in government or secure environments (desirable) 

Benefits

Why You'll Love Working Here:

Our company is more than just a workplace, it's a hub of inspiration and creativity where employees love to work! Here's why:

Hybrid working (for majority of our roles) with team anchor days to support collaboration
Extensive training and development opportunities that enable continual growth as part of your career planning
Extensive discounts and benefits to maximise your money
A choice of your IT equipment to maximise your success and access to cost-price tech for your personal needs
Fun team events to celebrate achievements and connect with colleagues outside work as part of our engaging culture

CT celebrates diversity and enables every voice to be heard as we drive to create the world we want. Apply today and be part of a team that values innovation, inclusivity, variety and diverse backgrounds.

Note: A valid Vulnerable People / Working with Children Check (WWCC) and Police Check are required.

